org.universAAL.ri.gateway

Class Exporter.NullConcurrentHashMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<String,Resource[]>
        • org.universAAL.ri.gateway.Exporter.NullConcurrentHashMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, ConcurrentMap<String,Resource[]>, Map<String,Resource[]>
    Enclosing class:
    Exporter

    public static class Exporter.NullConcurrentHashMap
extends ConcurrentHashMap<String,Resource[]>
    Helper class that wraps ConcurrentHashMap allowing for null values. Null values are internally converted to/from a token constant. Use getNullable and putNullable instead of the original get and put. It was done this way because get and put are used internally and should not be overridden.
    Author:
    alfiva
